Executive Profile
Bruce G. Bodaken  Director, iRhythm Technologies, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships65--
Background

		Mr. Bruce G. Bodaken served as the Chief Executive Officer and President at Blue Shield of California Life & Health Insurance Company. Mr. Bodaken served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of California Physicians' Service, Inc. (alternate name, Blue Shield of California) from January 2000 to December 2012 and its President from 1994 to June 1, 2012. He joined of California in 1994 and served as its Chief Operating Officer from 1996 to 2000. He served as Senior ... Vice President and Associate Chief Operating Officer of FHP International Corporation in Southern California. He served as the Chairman at Blue Shield of California Life & Health Insurance Company. He has been a Director of iRhythm Technologies, Inc. since July 17, 2017. He has been an Independent Director of Rite Aid Corporation since May 13, 2013. Mr. Bodaken has been an Independent Director at WageWorks, Inc. since September 2005. He also serves on the board of directors of the Institute of Medicine's Roundtable on Value and Science-Driven Healthcare and is a visiting scholar at the Brookings Institution. He serves on the Boards of California Business Roundtable, America's Health Insurance Plans and the University of California, Berkeley's Health Services Management Program. He is also a Member of the UCSF School of Pharmacy Dean's Board of Advisors. He served as Director of AltheaDx, Inc. since October 2014 and served as its Lead Independent Director since December 2014. Mr. Bodaken holds an M.A. in Philosophy from the University of Colorado and a B.A. in Philosophy from Colorado State University.Read Full Background




